content: but i am in aus now
I am glad to see you here!
I hope you are all doing well!
My admiration to those good fighters in the tournament who are playing their games with dedication.
I noticed that most of the games are over by now.
Any predictions of the winner of final yet?
And mumax will win the QT :)
mumax will be a teacher in theory department :)
Now, before we begin with analyses, lets warm up.
Last week, the cps were given to active students only,

dhalsim, coco_yuang, virag, Red_Zombie, tianxia, weigui, alcore, shuwang, sosei, smallpig, fallnavy, xiaoxuan, mayhem, leto, ouyang, Ikon, whte, renjunewbie, luwenzhe, bergamot, lingdodo, yyfcsd, HEX77.
so hopefully today everybody is active. :)
Today, I will introduce to you a strong Russian master,
Ilyin was beaten by chinesse players by memory playing :)
Ilyin was one of the greatest renju players ever in Russia.
Unfortunately, he distanced from active renju in around 1997.
He has achieved a lot in renju.
Ilyin and I are in about same age,
he is a few months older than me.
We first met when we were 15 years old.
At that time, I lost to him.
why did he give up renju?
and reached the peak of his career in 1995.
and was superior leader of the whole tournament.
Mr Kawamura and I were far behind him.
At that moment his dream was very close - almost everybody started to think he will win the WC 1995.
But he lost his last 3 games.
To me, to Nara, to Ants.
If he had won at least one of the three,
he would have won the WC title.
But even though he did not reach his biggest dream,
he proved everyone how strong he is,
and how big potential he has.
Next year, there was the team WC,
where Ilyin played on the first table of Russian team.
This was also the first time Chinese players took part in international tournament.
Anyway, it was the last time I had a chance to meet Ilyin.
Soon after that he retired from renju, because he had to move to another city, to enter university.
He had no time for renju anymore.
But maybe he will come back.
And he will show us is power again.
Today's game is from the 1996 Team World Championship.
I picked one of his win games.
And who was the white loser?
yamaguchi had retired at that time.
Actually, we played 4 games with each other at that tournament, some win some loss,
but here is his win game.
In group tournament, Russian and Estonian team met once, playing 2 rounds.
And later, in final we met again, 2 more rounds.
He chose blacks in i3, of course.
This 8th move was new style back then.
I hoped to surprise him by that.
Has anyone of you seen this 8th move before?
Where is the usual 8th move then?
Even though he was not prepared for the 8th move I played,
and is this 7 the strongest one?
The majority of people believed at that time
I had this win analysed in 1995.
it was played by yamaguchi as white
But nobody knew it for many years.
Because I didnt have a chance to play it.
I spent 75 minutes to find 11th move.
And Yamaguchi wrote number 75' on his hand,
And he said he will always remember I spent 75 minutes for this 11th move.
But 7 years ago, people did not think 7-k6 is good.
I thought. maybe he will put here
so I can play here myself
And I just defend and wait the attack to fade.
But this move was strong indeed.
I could not come up with anything better than 10-k5.
and I asked if you can suggest any better move
h7 possible, but maybe not better
g8, k8 my opinion but maybe worse
means, no win in that branch
You got some ideas about other 10th move now.
Let us have a check now.

luwenzhe, yyfcsd, Ikon, moocheng, bergamot, Red_Zombie, lingdodo, xiaoxuan, weigui, tianxia, dhalsim, mayhem, alcore, fallnavy, ouyang, shuwang, smallpig, Intotherenju, virag, renjunewbie, bawangwan, HEX77, whte, coco_yuang.
It scared me a lot when he began the outplay.
I spent quite some time to think over move 16.
if 16-k9 doesnt lose, then its best move
so its a question of win or loss here
ok, lets say once more, like voting.
didnt see such equally distributed answer for a long time :)
if K9 black will win by I4?
I forgot to add these two.
I am old and poor memory
is black win if white middle?
without 11 and 12, then white can defend
So, I was forced to play such a poor 18-k6.
Now he got the upper space for attack.
I thought over several choices of defense.
but it seemed unlikely that white could defend here.
In the game, I was afraid of L9 and m10
And white is defending with only possible moves.
Does black have straight win here?
Indeed, there is no direct win,
I had played good moves until this moment,
but now I began to play poorly.
Just when got the chance to do something,
Especially, when you spend lots of time on defense,
you have no strength to focus once more,
That happened to me in this game.
black had no attack power at i10,
because white's defense structure nearby was good already.
If move 28 immediately here, then he does not have too many choices.
and I might get that i10 point while he gets some weak point at the same time.
So, as for defense, 28-e8 was good,
something on right wing would be good,
in condition that the right wing move is a VCF threat.
If I play passive move here,
Then maybe some trouble may happen.
Anyway, I chose the poorest move.
and kill my right wing power,
having his left wing potential still available.
See how one poor move can chance the course of the whole game.
I played an active 30 now, but too late.
Furthermore, I made things worse for myself with that attack.
Now I continued my plan that I made with move 32,
I should have defended at e8 still.
Move 35 - black is attacking in white's territory.
so, I didnt have much choice at all.
I had to play such passive 36th move,
and you can see black gets now both j2 and m3 support
I was about to lose soon.
sorry ..late ..but I am in the library
Black skilfully brought the power from right all the way to the left,
This question seems hard for you.
but L3 not interesting, need defence and after that black has enogh power left side
Where I was white against Ilyin,
and got a loss from him.
It was a good lesson to me,
So, now, we will end the lesson.
And we will meet again soon!
alcore, bergamot, coco_yuang, dhalsim, Ikon, lingdodo, luwenzhe, mayhem, ouyang, Red_Zombie, renjunewbie, shuwang, tianxia, virag, weigui, whte, xiaoxuan, yyfcsd.
